A special edition weapon exclusively available during the Fifteenth Entropia New year (FEN) event.

The origin of this mid-level carbine is largely unknown, as the secrets and identity of the Isis Corporation has not yet been exposed. While more weapons from the mysterious organization turns up every now and then, CDF and otter military seems no closer to finding them. 

The LC-25, like many Isis weapons, has several similarities to GeoTrek weaponry, causing the latter to demand investigations about copyright issues.
Electrocutes the target, dealing powerful Electric damage over a long duration and lowers healing received by a short duration.

While some say this gun has just been 'cobbled together', that is actually far from the truth. There is a lot of thought behind this creation by MacMahon and his apprentice Rolan Durr, as well as many hours of component testing and fine tuning.

While most of the parts used in this design are old but improved, the energy conversion and focusing systems are state-of-the-art, causing the pistol to be both powerful and economical. Since this weapon uses a lot of modified parts, it is not compatible with Calypso repair terminals and can not be repaired.

Properties.Description: The Oblivion Protocol is a last-option directive of the robots of ARIS, ensuring total destruction of any assets that risk exposing their core systems. When activated, it initiates immediate annihilation of compromised installations, data, and entities. This scorched-earth policy reflects their cold logic: secrecy is paramount, and nothing is spared to protect their dominion. The Oblivion Protocol weapons line was created for this purpose, and reflects the directive's ruthless philosophy: absolute destruction with no trace left behind. Engineered by ARIS's Robot Overseers, these weapons combine advanced disintegration tech and adaptive AI, built to leave nothing behind -- erasing enemies, structures, and even data with extreme precaution. They are tools of war designed for secrecy through obliteration.
